         <div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">

<ab><lb n="1"/>  <persName type="divine"><name nymRef="#Ἀφροδίτη">Ἀφροδίτῃ</name></persName>  <w lemma="θεός">θεοῖς</w>  <persName type="emperor">Σεβαστοῖς</persName>  <lb n="2"/> <w lemma="ὁ">τῷ</w> <w lemma="δῆμος">Δήμῳ</w> <w lemma="ὁ">τὸ</w> <w lemma="ἄγαλμα">ἄγαλμα</w> <w lemma="ὁ">τοῦ</w> <w>Δή<lb n="3" break="no"/>μου</w>  <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Νικόμαχος">Νικόμαχος</name>  <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Μηνόδοτος">Μηνοδότου</name>  <lb n="4"/> <w lemma="ὁ">τοῦ</w> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Μένανδρος">Μενάνδρου</name></persName></persName></persName> <w lemma="καί">καὶ</w> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Μηνόδοτος">Μηνόδο<lb n="5" break="no"/>τος</name>  <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Νικόμαχος">Νικομάχου</name> <w lemma="ὁ">τοῦ</w> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Μηνόδοτος">Μηνοδό<lb n="6" break="no"/>του</name></persName></persName></persName> <w lemma="καθώς">καθὼς</w> <w lemma="ἐπαγγέλλω"><orig reg="ἐπηγγείλαντο">ἐπηνγίλαντο</orig></w>      <g ref="#star"/>  </ab>
</div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>For Aphrodite, the gods Augusti, the People: the statue of the People Nikomachos son of Menodotos the son of Menandros and Menodotos son of Nikomachos the son of Menodotos <supplied reason="subaudible">put up</supplied> as they promised.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Strictly the date should be after the deification of Livia Augusta, but it is possible to envisage a dedication of this sort in the east much earlier. On statues of Demos see <bibl>NPMilner, AS 38, (1988), 137</bibl>.</p>
            <p>For another dedication of a statue of Demos see <ref type="inscription" n="817" target="020111.xml"/> (=62.452) (mentioned by Erim and Smith)</p>
         </div>
         <div type="bibliography">
            <p>Published (in majuscule) with the statue, by <bibl>
                  <author>K.T. Erim &amp; R. R. R. Smith</author>, <title>Aphrodisias Papers</title> 2, 74</bibl>, whence <bibl n="seg">SEG <citedRange>1991.921</citedRange>
               </bibl>.</p>
         </div>
